721059f-b.text:
Lexington Avenue, east side, south from a point between 77th and 76th Streets to the S.E. corner of 74th Street. On the S.E. corner of 76th Street stands the Roman Catholic church Eglise St. Jean

The apartment house adjoining it was built in the 1920's on the site of three old houses similar to the two remaining on the N.E. corner
of 75th Street.
June 28, 1935.
